Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.88,0:00:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dr. David Hawkins. I've been a psychiatrist for 35 years, worked for many years in the field of psychoanalysis, all the various forms of individual and group psychotherapy, did years of research in psychopharmacology, also in nutrition and its relationship to brain chemistry, many years I worked with addiction, and for the last 10 years I've been working on research in the nature of consciousness itself and its application of that human field of knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.23,0:01:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge known as the spiritual. And so we've done a series of talks on utilizing a consciousness approach to a variety of man's problems, you know, stress, alcoholism, various diseases, depression, fear, major loss, and in those talks we've spent a great deal of time on the subject matter and a short amount of time on the map of consciousness that we've utilized in all of them to explain
